 for bestpractices and # User Profile & Account Management

## Overview
Build a secure, scalable User Profile & Account Management system for Gbox360 that enables user CRUD for profile editing, management of saved companies, preferences (including provisional weight scenarios), and account deletion/export with robust validation, re-authentication for sensitive actions, and GDPR-compliant data export. The feature set spans two pages (Settings & Preferences and User Profile) and supports a multi-faceted audit trail with raw payloads preserved for compliance. All frontend components must be resilient to null/undefined values and guard against non-array data when rendering lists. All data fetching from Supabase or APIs should follow the runtime safety rules outlined below.

## Components to Build
1) User Profile Page (page_core_010)
- Summary view of user metadata (avatar, name, email, membership status).
- Sectioned panels for:
  - Saved Companies (list with ability to add/remove).
  - Recent Activity (overview of recent profile changes and actions).
  - Weight Scenarios Preview (provisional weights with a live preview).
- Inline edit experiences (profile fields, password change with re-auth).
- Action controls: Save changes, Cancel, and a prominent Delete Account action (with multi-step confirmation).
- Data visualization scaffolding for provisional weight previews (non-sentiment, time-based previews).

2) Settings & Preferences Page (page_core_009)
- Profile Details editor (name, avatar, contact, timezone, language).
- Notification Preferences (email/push/SMS toggles, per-event granularity).
- Weight Scenario Toggles (provisional weights) with on/off and per-scenario weighting controls and a live preview summary.
- Data Export Preferences (format, scope, frequency, retention notes).
- Data Export/Download component (GDPR export with progress indicator and ability to download generated artifacts).
- Data deletion workflow controls (requires re-authentication and confirmation steps).

3) Backend User & Preferences API surface
- User CRUD endpoints (GET/PUT for profile data, PATCH for partial updates).
- Password change endpoint with current password verification and re-auth flow.
- Saved Companies management endpoints (GET list, POST add, DELETE remove).
- Preferences endpoints (GET/PUT for JSON preferences blob, validation).
- Weight Scenarios endpoints (GET provisional preview, POST to commit provisional or reset).
- Account Deletion endpoint with multi-step confirmation and re-auth validation.
- Data Export endpoint (initiates GDPR export job, returns downloadable artifact ZIP).
- Audit trail endpoints (CRUD-safe raw payload capture and retrieval).

4) Data Model & Audit
- Users table: id, email, name, avatar_url, locale, timezone, metadata JSON, preferences JSON, created_at, updated_at.
- SavedCompanies relation: user_id, company_id, saved_at.
- ProvisionalWeightScenarios: per-user, per-scenario weight config with versioning.
- RawPayloads/Audit: immutable append-only store for critical actions (profile updates, password changes, exports, deletions).
- Access control layer: ensure only authenticated user can access their own resources; admin overrides if applicable (not used in MVP).

5) Admin/Utility
- Export job dashboard/status API for GDPR export with progress reporting.
- Utility helpers for sanitization, field length checks, and normalization (e.g., name normalization, email normalization).
- Security utilities: re-auth enforcement, rate limiting for sensitive endpoints, MFA hooks (optional for MVP but design-ready).

## Implementation Requirements

### Frontend
- Framework/Stack: React with TypeScript, hooks, context for auth, and a clean component library alignment with the project’s design system.
- Routing: /settings (Settings & Preferences) and /profile (User Profile).
- UI Components to Build:
  - AvatarUploader: local preview, drag/drop support, server upload with error handling.
  - InlineEditableField: reusable label + input + save/cancel controls with optimistic UI updates.
  - ToggleGroup: for notification preferences and provisional weight toggles with per-item enable/disable.
  - ProvisionalWeightPreview: visual live calculation/results UI with numeric emphasis (large numbers for weights).
  - Card components: consistent with the design system (borders, shadows, hover states, paddings).
  - SavedCompaniesList: array rendering with add/remove actions; safeguard with Array.isArray(data) checks and nullish-coalescing.
  - ActivityTimeline: simple, accessible list with timestamps and action descriptions.
  - DataExportPanel: trigger export, show status, and provide download link when ready.
  - ConfirmationModal: multi-step (confirm action, re-auth prompt) for sensitive actions.
  - PasswordChangeCard: current password, new password, confirm password fields with strength meter.
  - Re-authModal: prompt for password or alternative auth factor as part of sensitive operations.
- State Management:
  - useState with proper defaults: useState<Type[]>([]) for arrays, useState<string>("") for strings where appropriate.
  - useEffect data fetches that defensively guard against nulls: const profile = data ?? {}; ensure arrays are guarded: const saved = Array.isArray(profile.savedCompanies) ? profile.savedCompanies : [].
  - Loaders and skeletons to handle pending API responses.
- Data Safety in UI:
  - Guard all array operations: (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : [].
  - Optional chaining everywhere API data is accessed: data?.field, payload?.nested?.field.
  - Provide sane defaults for all debounced/async updates to avoid undefined render cycles.
- Accessibility:
  - All inputs with labels, keyboard navigation, focus outlines, aria-live regions for status updates, and proper aria-expanded attributes on collapsible components.
- Validation:
  - Frontend input validation (max lengths, prohibited characters for names, valid email formats).
  - Debounced validations for unique email (if editable) and password strength checks.
- Security UX:
  - Re-auth workflows for password change and account deletion triggering a modal that requires current password (or available re-auth method).
  - CSRF-safe requests with auth tokens handled via existing API client.

### Backend
- API Design:
  - RESTful style with consistent endpoints, required authentication, and clear error messages.
  - Endpoints:
    - GET /api/users/me profile
    - PUT /api/users/me/profile
    - PATCH /api/users/me/profile
    - POST /api/users/me/password
    - GET /api/users/me/saved-companies
    - POST /api/users/me/saved-companies
    - DELETE /api/users/me/saved-companies/:companyId
    - GET /api/users/me/preferences
    - PUT /api/users/me/preferences
    - GET /api/users/me/provisional-weights/preview
    - POST /api/users/me/provisional-weights/commit
    - POST /api/users/me/export
    - POST /api/users/me/delete
  - Data validation: enforce max field lengths, sanitize inputs, prevent script injections, strip unwanted whitespace, validate locale/timezone codes.
  - Security:
    - Re-authentication for password changes and account deletion.
    - Authorization checks: ensure user_id matches the authenticated user.
    - Rate limiting on sensitive endpoints.
  - Supabase integration (assumed): 
    - Normalize results with data ?? [] for lists.
    - Guard against non-arrays before mapping.
- Database Tables:
  - users: id (PK), email (unique), name, avatar_url, locale, timezone, metadata JSON, preferences JSON, created_at, updated_at.
  - saved_companies: id (PK), user_id (FK), company_id, saved_at.
  - provisional_weight_scenarios: id (PK), user_id (FK), scenario_key, weights JSON, created_at, updated_at, is_provisional boolean.
  - audit_logs: id (PK), user_id, action_type, payload JSON, created_at.
  - exports: id (PK), user_id, status, artifact_url, created_at, updated_at.
- Data Export:
  - GDPR-compliant export bucket: generate ZIP containing user metadata, saved preferences, saved companies, audit payloads, and provisional weights history.
  - Endpoint returns a signed URL or artifact metadata; notify frontend on completion.
- Validation & Error Handling:
  - Validate all input shapes; provide fallback defaults if missing.
  - Normalize and sanitize strings; enforce maximum lengths (e.g., name 100 chars, locale 10 chars).
  - Audit changes on every sensitive operation and store raw payloads.

### Integration
- Data Flow:
  - Frontend calls API endpoints; API returns data guarded with data ?? [] and Array.isArray checks; UI renders only arrays.
  - When fetching user profile, merge defaults with fetched data to ensure stable rendering.
  - Provisional weight previews are client-driven computations based on current weights with a reconciliation call to fetch latest baseline data when needed.
- Error Propagation:
  - Consistent error shapes: { error: string, code?: string, details?: any }.
  - Frontend shows user-friendly messages; critical failures trigger toast/error banner with actionable steps.
- Data Integrity:
  - All mutations write to audit_logs with a payload containing the request body and user context.
  - Retry logic for transient failures with exponential backoff on critical mutations.

## User Experience Flow
1) User lands on Settings & Preferences
- Sees Profile Details with editable fields (name, avatar, locale, timezone).
- Adjusts Notification Preferences via toggles.
- Enables/disables Provisional Weight Scenarios with per-scenario weight sliders and a live “Preview” summary showing projected impact.
- Configures Data Export Preferences (format, scope, cadence).
- Clicks Export GDPR Data; initiation banner appears with status and estimated completion; download link presented on completion.
- Optional: Initiate account deletion with a multi-step confirmation flow; re-auth required; success leads to a final confirmation screen.
2) User lands on User Profile
- Overview card shows avatar, name, email, account age.
- Saved Companies section shows a list with search, add, and remove functionality.
- Recent Activity timeline lists last 5 actions with timestamps.
- Weight Scenarios Preview card shows provisional weights and a “What changed?” drill-down capability to view contributing events or data points.
- Password Change panel prompts for current password, new password, and confirmation; re-auth prompt if required.
- Export/Delete actions appear in the bottom-right of the page as safe, clearly labeled actions.

## Technical Specifications

Data Models: [Schema details]
- Users
  - id: string (PK)
  - email: string (unique)
  - name: string
  - avatar_url: string | null
  - locale: string
  - timezone: string
  - metadata: JSON
  - preferences: JSON
  - created_at: timestamp
  - updated_at: timestamp
- SavedCompanies
  - id: string (PK)
  - user_id: string (FK to Users.id)
  - company_id: string
  - saved_at: timestamp
- ProvisionalWeightScenarios
  - id: string (PK)
  - user_id: string (FK)
  - scenario_key: string
  - weights: JSON
  - is_provisional: boolean
  - created_at: timestamp
  - updated_at: timestamp
- AuditLogs
  - id: string (PK)
  - user_id: string
  - action_type: string
  - payload: JSON
  - created_at: timestamp
- Exports
  - id: string (PK)
  - user_id: string
  - status: string (pending/completed/failed)
  - artifact_url: string | null
  - created_at: timestamp
  - updated_at: timestamp

API Endpoints: [Routes and methods]
- GET /api/users/me/profile
- PUT /api/users/me/profile
- PATCH /api/users/me/profile
- POST /api/users/me/password
- GET /api/users/me/saved-companies
- POST /api/users/me/saved-companies
- DELETE /api/users/me/saved-companies/:companyId
- GET /api/users/me/preferences
- PUT /api/users/me/preferences
- GET /api/users/me/provisional-weights/preview
- POST /api/users/me/provisional-weights/commit
- POST /api/users/me/export
- POST /api/users/me/delete
- GET /api/audit/logs?range=recent
- GET /api/exports/:exportId

Security: Authentication, authorization requirements
- JWT or session-based auth with secure HttpOnly cookies.
- Endpoints require authentication; sensitive actions (password change, account deletion, data export) require re-auth verification (password or MFA token if configured).
- Role-based access if admin capabilities exist (not required for MVP).
- Input validation, CSRF protection where applicable, rate limiting for critical endpoints.

Validation: Input validation rules
- Name: required, 1–100 chars; strip leading/trailing whitespace.
- Email: valid email format, immutable after account creation (unless re-verification is supported).
- Avatar URL: valid URL or data URL; enforce size limits on uploads.
- Locale/Timezone: valid IANA/Zones or supported subset.
- Notification preferences: boolean toggles; ensure defaults enabled where appropriate.
- Weights: numeric values within defined bounds (e.g., 0–1 or 0–100 per weight), maintain sum constraints if required.
- Password: minimum length, complexity rules, match confirmation, password history checks (optional).

Acceptance Criteria
- [ ] All frontend components render safely with missing/undefined data; all array operations guarded: (items ?? []).map(...) and Array.isArray checks.
- [ ] Profile data fetch returns data guarded with defaults; UI renders without crashes even with partial data.
- [ ] Provisional weight previews update in real-time with valid inputs and do not crash on edge cases.
- [ ] Re-auth flow triggers for password changes and account deletion; operations fail securely if re-auth canceled.
- [ ] GDPR export generates a ZIP with user data; download link is provided; export job status is observable.
- [ ] Deleted account removes user data and generates audit trail; cannot access profile after deletion.
- [ ] All API responses sanitized; errors mapped to user-friendly messages with actionable steps.

UI/UX Guidelines
Apply the project's design system:
- See Visual Style guidelines provided below for color, typography, spacing, and component treatment.
- Maintain enterprise-grade polish: precise spacing, subtle shadows, accessible contrast, and predictable transitions.
- Ensure fast scannability: clear typographic hierarchy, prominent actions, and digestible data chunks.
- Emphasize data provenance, auditability, and transparency in UI cues (badges, provenance chips, and raw-payload displays where appropriate).

Visual Style

Color Palette (as provided)
- Primary background: #FBFBFC
- Map/background overlay: #F3F4F6
- Primary text: #111827
- Secondary text / meta: #6B7280
- Borders / dividers: #E5E7EB
- Card background / surfaces: #FFFFFF
- Accent (callouts / badges): #FF6B4A
- Accent (interactive / primary CTA): #0F172A
- Accent (focus / subtle highlights): #93C5FD
- Muted success/credibility accent: #10B981

Typography & Layout
- Font family: Inter / SF Pro / system-ui
- H1: 48–56px, weight 700
- H2: 24–32px, weight 600–700
- Body: 16px, weight 400, line-height 1.4–1.6
- Micro/metadata: 12–14px, weight 500/400, color #6B7280
- Numeric stats: 28–36px, weight 700
- Grid: 12-column, generous vertical rhythm, 48–64px between major sections
- Card paddings: 20–28px; controls: 12–16px

Key Design Elements
- Card: white surface with 1px border #E5E7EB, radius 10–12px, soft shadow, hover lift.
- Navigation: top bar with brand left, center/left links, auth actions right; active state underline or accent dot.
- Data Visualization: minimal, line charts with accent colors; soft grid lines (#F3F4F6).
- Interactive Elements: primary CTAs #0F172A; secondary controls; focus outlines #93C5FD.
- Accessibility: clear focus-visible states; aria attributes for collapsible sections; accessible labels for all controls.

Mandatory Coding Standards — Runtime Safety

CRITICAL: Follow these rules in ALL generated code to prevent runtime crashes.

1) Supabase query results:
- Always use nullish coalescing: const items = data ?? [].
2) Array methods:
- Guard with (items ?? []).map(...) or Array.isArray(items) ? items.map(...) : [].
3) React useState for arrays/objects:
- Initialize with correct type: useState<Type[]>([]).
4) API response shapes:
- const list = Array.isArray(response?.data) ? response.data : [].
5) Optional chaining:
- Use obj?.property?.nested when accessing API-derived objects.
6) Destructuring with defaults:
- const { items = [], count = 0 } = response ?? {}.

Project Context Notes
- Target Feature: User Profile & Account Management
- Focus: User CRUD for profile editing, saved companies, preferences (including provisional weights), provisional weight previews, account deletion/export.
- Associated Pages: page_core_009 (Settings & Preferences), page_core_010 (User Profile)
- Platform: Gbox360 — Investor Perception Index & Narrative Intelligence
- Ingress/Canary: Ensure export and deletion flows are robust, auditable, and user-consented.

Deliverables
- Fully typed React components and hooks for the two pages (Settings & Preferences, User Profile) with integrated API clients.
- Backend API routes described above with validation, sanitization, and security hooks.
- Supabase-compatible data access patterns with null safety (data ?? []) and array guards.
- Comprehensive tests (unit and integration) covering:
  - Profile fetch and update flows with partial/missing fields
  - Guarded rendering of lists (saved companies, activity)
  - Provisional weight preview dynamics
  - Re-auth flows for sensitive actions
  - GDPR export sequencing and artifact availability
  - Account deletion privacy and audit trail generation
- Documentation on API contracts, data schemas, and developer setup instructions.

This prompt aims to guide an AI development tool to generate a complete, production-ready implementation that adheres to the runtime safety rules, security requirements, UX guidelines, and the project’s design system. for style.

CRITICAL DESIGN REQUIREMENTS:
- You MUST follow ALL design principles and patterns specified in the Design Reference above
- Do NOT deviate from the design specifications without explicit user permission
- Implement ALL visual design elements (colors, typography, spacing, shadows, animations) as specified
- Follow the layout patterns and component designs exactly as documented
- Ensure all interactions and micro-animations match the reference specifications

CRITICAL TECHNICAL REQUIREMENTS:
- React 18.3.1, React Router 6.30.1
- Tailwind CSS v3 with tailwind.config.js and custom keyframes
- @tailwindcss/typography plugin for rich text content
- Tailwind CSS animations (NOT Motion library or framer-motion)
- Sonner for toasts
- Recharts for data visualization
